From a5a749e1846d3029bd5749650d18069c1471991b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Gemini Mainline Experiment <gemini-mainline@example.invalid>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 13:31:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 80/81] arm64: dts: mediatek: gemini: add ramoops backend

The shipping Gemini software reserves 0xe0000 bytes at 0x44410000 for
pstore.  The running Gemian kernel exposes the same region through a
modified ramoops driver with 0x1000-byte crash records and 0x10000-byte
console and pmsg sizes.  It also uses a 0x1000-byte ftrace size,
write-combined mappings, and no ECC.

That downstream driver reserves two console-size zones, unlike upstream.
Its exact active binary gives both console records ID zero, so a record in
the second zone can be hidden by a duplicate filename.  Use an otherwise
unconsumed 0x20000-byte pmsg allocation to align the upstream dmesg and
primary console ranges with their downstream counterparts.  Even with
CONFIG_PSTORE_PMSG=n, ramoops performs its PRZ_FLAG_ZAP_OLD single-zone
initialization for that allocation.  Probe may therefore snapshot the old
contents and clear the inherited downstream bconsole header.  The disabled
frontend prevents subsequent pmsg payload writes.  This allocation is never
cross-version pmsg evidence.

The board DT currently reserves the range but does not instantiate a pstore
backend.  A mainline kernel therefore cannot yet leave console output for
the known-good Gemian system to recover after a warm reset.  Describe the
observed parameters without changing the reservation.
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797-gemini-pda.dts | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797-gemini-pda.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797-gemini-pda.dts
index 605090f6e..f829a6d06 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797-gemini-pda.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797-gemini-pda.dts
@@ -56,8 +56,14 @@ memory@44400000 {
 			no-map;
 		};
 
-		memory@44410000 {
+		ramoops@44410000 {
+			compatible = "ramoops";
 			reg = <0 0x44410000 0 0xe0000>;
+			record-size = <0x1000>;
+			console-size = <0x10000>;
+			ftrace-size = <0x1000>;
+			pmsg-size = <0x20000>;
+			mem-type = <0>;
 			no-map;
 		};
 
